o4-mini Answer:
First factor and cancel common factors in coefficients and like bases:

\[
\frac{24\,r^3\,s}{6\,r^2\,s^7}
=\frac{24}{6}\,\frac{r^3}{r^2}\,\frac{s}{s^7}
=4\,r^{3-2}\,s^{1-7}
=4\,r\,s^{-6}
=\frac{4r}{s^6}.
\]

o3 Answer:
Apply the negative-exponent rule, a^{-n}=1/a^{n}.

(2y)^{-3}=1/(2y)^{3}

Now cube the factors inside the parentheses:

(2y)^{3}=2^{3}·y^{3}=8y^{3}

So

(2y)^{-3}=1/(8y^{3}).
